      "date": "2011-11-30 22:32:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Do not submit\n\n(5 inline comments)\n\nCan you please resubmit this with the original Change-Id: line so that it is possible to compare this patch against the earlier ones.  This change should be abandoned in favour of change 1111.\n\nIs it too bad that there was no indication in the bug or anywhere else that you were also working on an updated version of this kernel patch, since it means duplicated effort on both of our parts.  I thought you were only working on the e2fsprogs code, based on your comments in LU-80.\n\nI would actually prefer if this patch were split into separate pieces, for ldiskfs large xattrs (this change 1111), the client code (change 1194), and the RPC size changes (a new change).  This will make inspection considerably easier.",
