          "email": "alexander_boyko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2011-11-30 19:12:29.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-80 striping: large stripe count support",
        "message": "LU-80 striping: large stripe count support\n\nCurrently a file can be stripped across OSTs up to a limit of\n160 stripes. This patch expands that limit to 2000 and it is\npossible to go even to larger stripe counts. The patch applies\nagainst both RHEL5 and RHEL6.\nThis patch differs from Yu Jian`s patch in:\n1) Fixed endians in the ext4 patch\n2) Removed changes not related to wide stripe\n3) Maximum OST number increased up to 2K\n4) Reply buffer size shrinking removed,\nbecause no client side support for this code\n5) Fixed MDS buffer size\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander_boyko@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I6f13d709be2b2e5a0b06127ed99730462295630a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
